1172			; https://tutorials.eeems.ca/ASMin28Days/lesson/day16.html#cmp 
1172			 
1172			; String Length 
1172			;With a length-prefixed string, finding the length is trivial. For a null-terminated string, the process is decidedly more involved. This is where CPIR comes in. 
1172			 
1172			; Get the length of the null-terminated string starting at $8000 hl 
1172			;    LD     HL, $8000 
1172			 
1172			strlenz: 
1172			 
1172 af			    XOR    A               ; Zero is the value we are looking for. 
1173 47			    LD     B, A             ; Since we haven't the slightest clue as to the  
1174 4f			    LD     C, A             ; actual size of the string, put 0 in BC to search 
1175			                           ; 65, 536 bytes (the entire addressable memory space). 
1175 ed b1		    CPIR                   ; Begin search for a byte equalling zero. 
1177			 
1177			; BC has been decremented so that it holds -length. Now need to synthesize a NEG BC. 
1177 67			    LD     H, A             ; Zero HL (basically set it to 65, 536) to get the 
1178 6f			    LD     L, A             ; number of bytes 
1179 ed 42		    SBC    HL, BC           ; Find the size. CPIR doesn't affect carry. 
117b 2b			    DEC    HL              ; Compensate for null. 
117c c9				ret 
117d			 
117d			; Get the length of the A terminated string starting at $8000 hl 
117d			;    LD     HL, $8000 
117d			 
117d			strlent: 
117d			 
117d			                  ; A is the value we are looking for. 
117d 06 00		    LD     B, 0             ; Since we haven't the slightest clue as to the  
117f 0e 00		    LD     C, 0             ; actual size of the string, put 0 in BC to search 
1181			                           ; 65, 536 bytes (the entire addressable memory space). 
1181 ed b1		    CPIR                   ; Begin search for a byte equalling zero. 
1183			 
1183			; BC has been decremented so that it holds -length. Now need to synthesize a NEG BC. 
1183 26 00		    LD     H, 0             ; Zero HL (basically set it to 65, 536) to get the 
1185 2e 00		    LD     L, 0             ; number of bytes 
1187 ed 42		    SBC    HL, BC           ; Find the size. CPIR doesn't affect carry. 
1189 2b			    DEC    HL              ; Compensate for null. 
118a c9				ret 
